f the radiation patterns of the elements in the array, the proposed approach is verified to enhance the scanning capacity of the array in detail. Two 1~8 linear arrays and one 8~8 planar array are demonstrated, which VOLUME 2, 2021 211 YANG et al.: WIDE-BAND AND WIDE-ANGLE SCANNING PHASED ARRAY ANTENNA FOR MOBILE COMMUNICATION SYSTEM achieve the large scanning coverage of around }60. but a realized gain reduction under 3.5 dB in the band from 3.15 to 4.6 GHz (37.4%). Furthermore, the beam in the E-plane can scan more than }70. with a realized gain reduction under 3 dB. Two linear array prototypes for wide-angle scanning capacity in the H- and E-plane are fabricated and characterized, yielding good performance with overall operational bandwidth. The wide band phased array with large scanning coverage can be realized by the proposed approach and applied in mobile communication system. REFERENCES [1] N. Amitay, V. Galindo, and C. P. Wu, Theory and Analysis of Phased Array Antennas. New York, NY, USA: Wiley-Intersci., 1972. [2] J. Zhang, X. Ge, Q. Li, M. Guizani, and Y. Zhang, g5G millimeterwave antenna array: Design and challenges,h IEEE Wireless Commun., vol. 24, no. 2, pp. 106.112, Apr. 2007. [3] S. E. Valavan, D. Tran, A. G. Yarovoy, and A. G. Roederer, gPlanar dual-band wide-scan phased array in X-band,h IEEE Trans. Antennas Propag., vol. 62, no. 10, pp. 5370.5375, Oct. 2014. [4] R. Wang, B. Z. Wang, C. Hu, and X. Ding, gWide-angle scanning planar array with quasi-hemispherical-pattern elements,h Sci. Rep., vol. 7, no. 1, p. 2729, Jun. 2017. [5] G. Yang, J. Li, S. G. Zhou, and Y. Qi, gA wide-angle scanning E-plane linear array antenna with wide beam elements,h IEEE Antennas Wireless Propag. Lett., vol. 16, pp. 2923.2926, Oct. 2017. [6] A. Kedar and K. S. Beenamole, gWide beam tapered slot antenna for wide-angle scanning phased array antenna,h Progr. Electromagn. Res. B, vol. 8, no. 1, pp. 235.251, 2011. [7] K. S. Beenamole, P. N. S. Kutiyal, U. K. Rev